<Issue id="13828" key="FAB-1419" number="1419" project="10002" reporter="kchristidis" assignee="kchristidis" creator="kchristidis" type="10002" summary="Set appropriate acknowledgement level" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2016-12-15 19:54:12.0" updated="2018-07-20 14:11:03.0" resolutiondate="2016-12-16 15:44:57.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="36897"> <description><! CDATA By default the partition leader (i.e. the Kafka broker responsible for maintainig a chain) waits only for the local commit to succeed before responding.  The right setting to maximize the reliability of data delivery is to have the partition leader wait for all in-sync replicas (backups) to get a message before sending back to the producer an acknowledgement or an error.  Thanks to  ~bcbrock  for bringing this to my attention.  ></description> </Issue>
